<td>
<h2>Xingbo Wu (吴兴博)</h2>
I'm an Assistant Professor at
<a href=https://www.cs.uic.edu/>University of Illinois at Chicago, Department of Computer Science</a>.
[<a href=https://bits.lab.uic.edu>BITS Laboratory</a>]
<br />
[wuxb@uic.edu]
[<a href=cv.pdf>CV</a>]
<br />
I earned my Ph.D. from <a href=https://cse.uta.edu>UTA CSE</a>, advised by <a href=http://ranger.uta.edu/~sjiang/>Dr. Song Jiang</a>.
<br />
<br />
</td>
</tbody>
</table>

My research focuses on computer systems. I am interested in NoSQL databases,
memory and storage, OS, and virtualization.
<br />
<b>I'm looking for motivated MS/PhD students interested in computer systems research.
If you're interested please send me your CV and transcripts.</b>

<h3>Teaching</h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <a href=https://sites.google.com/view/cs461fall2018/home>CS 461/491: Operating Systems Design and Implementation, Fall 2018</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    CS 594: Special Topics: High-performance NoSQL Databases, Spring 2019
  </li>
</ul>

